 PCB may go the BCCI way
Karachi: Some members of the newly constituted governing body of the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) want its players and selectors to stop writing columns or appearing on television channels in India. When the Indian board does not allow its players and selectors to earn money from writing columns or doing exclusive talk shows on television, why is our board being so lenient with our players. We feel these things are a distraction and has affected the performance of the team in India, a senior member of the governing body said on Thursday. The governing body has been constituted under the new constitution of the PCB and includes former Test players, representatives of affiliated regional associations, departments and some technocrats. (PTI) 
